Late into the evening of October 9, peaceful Egyptian protesters were attacked and at least 24 people were killed and more than 200 wounded; during protest that was held in Maspiro. <ref>http://www.bbc.co.uk/news/world-middle-east-15235212</ref>. The protest started due to an attack on a [[Coptic Orthodox Church of Alexandria|Coptic Christian]] church in Merinab village in [[Aswan]] on September 30. <ref>http://english.alarabiya.net/articles/2011/10/09/170992.html</ref> Aswan governor '''Mustafa al-Seyyed''' said that Copts had built the church without having the proper permits. <ref>http://english.alarabiya.net/articles/2011/10/09/170992.html</ref>. The October 9 attack was committed by both the Egyptian police force and military police<ref>http://www.arabawy.org/2011/10/09/army-and-police-massacre-protesters-at-maspero/</ref> using live ammunition<ref>http://www.guardian.co.uk/world/middle-east-live/2011/oct/10/egypt-libya-middle-east-unrest-live?CMP=NECNETTXT8187</ref>, vehicles to run over protesters<ref>http://www.montrealgazette.com/news/Church+clash+turns+deadly+Cairo/5526557/story.html</ref> and extensive rounds of tear gas were fired<ref>http://www.arabawy.org/2011/10/09/army-and-police-massacre-protesters-at-maspero/</ref>.
â
The violence that would take place in Oct 9 had been committed by both the Egyptian Police force and military persons. Using live ammunition and vehicles running over protesters and extensive rounds of tear gas were fired; with showers of beatings from the military police and the central security forces. The Army also stormed Al-Hurra TV station and 25 January TV stations, and took them off air.
